The paper discusses the use of memristive devices in neuromorphic circuits, which falls under the category of neural networks and artificial intelligence (cs.NE). The paper also focuses on the electrical modeling of the memristive device, which can be categorized under electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET) and electromagnetics (cs.EM). The use of nanotechnology in the fabrication of the devices suggests the possibility of materials science (cs.MS) being a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of simulation tools for circuit analysis, which can be categorized under computer engineering (cs.CE).
